<figureCitation box="[158,324,1438,1462]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 32" captionStart-1="FIGURE 33" captionStartId-0="41.[151,250,1518,1541]" captionStartId-1="42.[151,250,1147,1170]" captionTargetBox-0="[151,1436,519,1496]" captionTargetBox-1="[152,1434,187,1137]" captionTargetId-0="figure-153@41.[151,1436,519,1496]" captionTargetId-1="figure-263@42.[151,1436,185,1137]" captionTargetPageId-0="41" captionTargetPageId-1="42" captionText-0="FIGURE 32. Oral view of Metridium farcimen showing stiffened lobes of oral disc (KUIZ 001436)." captionText-1="FIGURE 33. Distribution of Metridium farcimen from Mexico to Russia." pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Figures 32–33</figureCitation>
, Appendix 14)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,595,1403,1498]" box="[151,595,1474,1498]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
Synonyms: see 
<bibRefCitation author="Fautin, D. G. &amp; Hand, C." box="[326,595,1474,1498]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" pagination="1151 - 1161" refId="ref24418" refString="Fautin, D. G. &amp; Hand, C. (2000) Metridium farcimen, the valid name of a common North Pacific sea anemone (Cnidaria: Actiniaria: Acontiaria). Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 113 (4), 1151 - 1161." type="journal article" year="2000">Fautin and Hand (2000)</bibRefCitation>
</paragraph>
